snippet: The American Airlines plane, with 147 passengers heading from Phoenix to Boston, landed safety shortly after 7 a.m. on Monday.
abstract: Co-pilot of American Airlines plane carrying 147 passengers, en route from Phoenix to Boston, performs emergency landing in Syracuse after pilot falls ill and dies.
lead_paragraph: The American Airlines plane, with 147 passengers heading from Phoenix to Boston, landed safety shortly after 7 a.m. on Monday.

headline.main: Jet Makes Emergency Landing in Syracuse After Pilot Dies
headline.print_headline: Co-Pilot Lands Jet in Syracuse After Pilot Dies
